# Cloudflare Pages merges _headers rules CUMULATIVELY and joins duplicate
# header names with a comma. A `Cache-Control` on `/*` therefore gets prepended
# to the asset rules below, so browsers read `max-age=0, must-revalidate` FIRST
# and ignore `immutable` — forcing content-hashed fonts/CSS/JS to revalidate on
# every navigation (a blocking round-trip per asset that tanks real-user mobile
# TTFB/LCP). Unsetting with `! Cache-Control` does NOT work here (verified on a
# preview deploy). The only reliable fix: never set Cache-Control on `/*`, and
# scope the HTML policy to explicit HTML paths so each URL is matched by exactly
# ONE Cache-Control-setting rule.

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

# --- HTML pages: edge-cache 1 day, browser revalidates (unchanged policy) ---
# Root-level pages (build.format:'file' serves these at clean paths)
/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate, s-maxage=86400, stale-while-revalidate=604800
/about
